      <img src="/static9/us/2024/08/18/pesticides-may-remain-on-fruit-even-after-washing-study-finds.webp" alt="Pesticides may remain on fruit even after washing, study finds"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Pesticides may remain on fruit even after washing, study finds</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      According to a study published in August, merely washing fruit is not sufficient to remove residual pesticides and toxic chemicals.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/us/2024/08/18/pesticides-may-remain-on-fruit-even-after-washing-study-finds/"  >(Patrick Djordjevic, KTLA 5)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div></div></fieldset><fieldset><legend><h2>
        <a href="/world/">Around the world</a>
        </h2></legend>
        <div class="row"><div class="column text"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 15 Aug 2024 16:25:40 -0400">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 15 Aug 2024 16:25:40 -0400">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Fox News">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/world/2024/08/15/protests-sweep-india-rape-murder-doctor.webp" alt="Protests sweep India over rape and murder of doctor"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Protests sweep India over rape and murder of doctor</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      The rape and murder of a 31-year-old trainee doctor in India has sparked nationwide protests, with hundreds of thousands of women marching in cities across the South Asian country.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/08/15/protests-sweep-india-rape-murder-doctor/"  >(Fox News)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Sun, 18 Aug 2024 17:18:31 -0400">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Sun, 18 Aug 2024 17:18:31 -0400">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Fox News">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/world/2024/08/18/blinken-arrives-middle-east-renew-cease-fire-negotiations-gaza.webp" alt="Blinken arrives in Middle East to renew cease-fire negotiations in Gaza"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Blinken arrives in Middle East to renew cease-fire negotiations in Gaza</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Secretary of State Antony Blinken arrived in the Middle East on Sunday ahead of a renewed push for a cease-fire deal between Israel and Hamas.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/08/18/blinken-arrives-middle-east-renew-cease-fire-negotiations-gaza/"  >(Fox News)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Mon, 19 Aug 2024 05:57:22 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Mon, 19 Aug 2024 05:57:22 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="JOSEPH KRAUSS, Associated Press, PIX 11">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/world/2024/08/19/what-is-the-latest-on-the-high-stakes-negotiations-over-a-cease-fire-in-gaza.webp" alt="What is the latest on the high-stakes negotiations over a cease-fire in Gaza?"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">What is the latest on the high-stakes negotiations over a cease-fire in Gaza?</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      U.S. and Arab mediators say they are closing in on a deal to halt the war in Gaza and free hostages captured by Hamas in its Oct. 7 attack, but the talks have dragged on for months, with several moments of false hope.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/08/19/what-is-the-latest-on-the-high-stakes-negotiations-over-a-cease-fire-in-gaza/"  >(JOSEPH KRAUSS, Associated Press, PIX 11)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div><div class="column hcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Sun, 18 Aug 2024 20:40:57 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Sun, 18 Aug 2024 20:40:57 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Miranda Nazzaro, The Hill">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/world/2024/08/18/un-watchdog-extremely-concerned-about-safety-at-russia-controlled-nuclear-power-plant-in-ukraine.webp" alt="UN watchdog 'extremely concerned' about safety at Russian-controlled nuclear power plant in Ukraine"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">UN watchdog 'extremely concerned' about safety at Russian-controlled nuclear power plant in Ukraine</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      The safety situation at Ukraine’s Zaporizhzhia Nuclear Power Plant (ZNPP) is "deteriorating" after a nearby drone strike, the United Nations's energy watchdog said Saturday. The Russian military has occupied the plant since early March 2022, weeks after Moscow's initial invasion of Ukraine.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/08/18/un-watchdog-extremely-concerned-about-safety-at-russia-controlled-nuclear-power-plant-in-ukraine/"  >(Miranda Nazzaro, The Hill)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Mon, 19 Aug 2024 01:43:40 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Mon, 19 Aug 2024 01:43:40 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Associated Press, PIX 11">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/world/2024/08/19/ukrainian-troops-have-struck-2-key-bridges-in-russia-could-it-mean-theyre-there-to-stay.webp" alt="Ukrainian president says push into Russia's Kursk region is to create a buffer zone there"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Ukrainian president says push into Russia's Kursk region is to create a buffer zone there</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      KYIV, Ukraine (AP) — Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said Sunday the daring military incursion into Russia’s Kursk region aims to create a buffer zone to prevent further attacks by Moscow across the border.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/08/19/ukrainian-troops-have-struck-2-key-bridges-in-russia-could-it-mean-theyre-there-to-stay/"  >(Associated Press, PIX 11)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Wed, 14 Aug 2024 18:20:47 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Wed, 14 Aug 2024 18:20:47 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="MARIA CHENG, Associated Press, NewsNation">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/world/2024/08/14/who-declares-mpox-outbreaks-in-africa-a-global-health-emergency-as-a-new-form-of-the-virus-spreads.webp" alt="WHO declares mpox outbreaks in Africa a global health emergency as a new form of the virus spreads"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">WHO declares mpox outbreaks in Africa a global health emergency as a new form of the virus spreads</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      LONDON (AP) — The World Health Organization declared the mpox outbreaks in Congo and elsewhere in Africa a global emergency on Wednesday, with cases confirmed among children and adults in more than a dozen countries and a new form of the virus spreading.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/08/14/who-declares-mpox-outbreaks-in-africa-a-global-health-emergency-as-a-new-form-of-the-virus-spreads/"  >(MARIA CHENG, Associated Press, NewsNation)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div><div class="column vcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 15 Aug 2024 03:04:25 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 15 Aug 2024 03:04:25 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="MARI YAMAGUCHI, Associated Press, NewsNation">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/world/2024/08/15/explainer-japans-prime-minister-prepares-to-step-down-why-and-whats-next.webp" alt="Here's what's next in Japan with Kishida bowing out as party leader and prime minister next month"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Here's what's next in Japan with Kishida bowing out as party leader and prime minister next month</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      TOKYO (AP) — Japan's embattled Prime Minister Fumio Kishida surprised the country Wednesday by announcing that he'll step down when his party picks a new leader next month.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/08/15/explainer-japans-prime-minister-prepares-to-step-down-why-and-whats-next/"  >(MARI YAMAGUCHI, Associated Press, NewsNation)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div></div></fieldset><fieldset><legend><h2>
        <a href="/tech/">Technology</a>
        </h2></legend>
        <div class="row"><div class="column vcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Fri, 16 Aug 2024 20:28:08 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Fri, 16 Aug 2024 20:28:08 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Cameron Duran, The Mercury News">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/16/california-bill-to-regulate-ai-advances-over-tech-opposition-with-some-tweaks.webp" alt="California bill to regulate AI advances over tech opposition with some tweaks"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">California bill to regulate AI advances over tech opposition with some tweaks</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      AI regulation bill SB 1047 passed another legislative hurdle Thursday as the State Assembly's Appropriations Committee voted to approve an amended version of the bill.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/16/california-bill-to-regulate-ai-advances-over-tech-opposition-with-some-tweaks/"  >(Cameron Duran, The Mercury News)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div><div class="column text"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 15 Aug 2024 00:07:37 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 15 Aug 2024 00:07:37 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="MICHAEL LIEDTKE, Associated Press, KREX 5">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/15/judge-tells-google-to-brace-for-shakeup-of-android-app-store-as-punishment-for-running-a-monopoly.webp" alt="Judge tells Google to brace for shakeup of Android app store as punishment for running a monopoly"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Judge tells Google to brace for shakeup of Android app store as punishment for running a monopoly</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      SAN FRANCISCO (AP) — A federal judge on Wednesday indicated he will order major changes in Google’s Android app store to punish the company for engineering a system that a jury declared an illegal monopoly that has hurt millions of consumers and app developers.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/15/judge-tells-google-to-brace-for-shakeup-of-android-app-store-as-punishment-for-running-a-monopoly/"  >(MICHAEL LIEDTKE, Associated Press, KREX 5)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Fri, 16 Aug 2024 00:57:30 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Fri, 16 Aug 2024 00:57:30 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Computer World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/16/researchers-tackle-ai-fact-checking-failures-with-new-llm-training-technique.webp" alt="Researchers tackle AI fact-checking failures with new LLM training technique"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Researchers tackle AI fact-checking failures with new LLM training technique</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      As the excitement about the immense potential of large language models (LLMs) dies down, now comes the hard work of ironing out the things they don’t do well.  
The word “hallucination” is the most obvious example, but at least output that is crazily fictitious stands out as wrong.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/16/researchers-tackle-ai-fact-checking-failures-with-new-llm-training-technique/"  >(Computer World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Wed, 14 Aug 2024 22:19:43 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Wed, 14 Aug 2024 22:19:43 +0000">
